bilingual.source: I broke my leg falling on the ice.
He's hit his head and his leg hurts.
I hurt my leg when I was playing football.
My leg hurts, and I can't see very well.
Panpan, point to your arm and your leg.
bilingual.target: 潘潘，指向你的手臂和腿。

bilingual.source: My knee and my ankle are part of my leg.
bilingual.target: 我的膝盖和脚踝是腿的一部分。

list.abstract: 比赛中的一局。LEG = LIQUID ETHYLENE GAS （液化乙烯气体） ，同LNG（液化天然气）,LPG（液化石油气），同属于液化气系列leg

yingyinNormal.en: I got your leg. I got your leg!
yingyinNormal.zh: 我抓住你腿了 我抓住你腿了！

yingyinNormal.en: Joey told you about the leg, huh? Uh-huh.
yingyinNormal.zh: 乔伊跟你说过那条腿的事了？

yingyinNormal.en: Heard about the leg burning? It came up.
yingyinNormal.zh: 听过火烧腿的事了吧？她提过。

yingyinNormal.en: Who wants the Teddy bear with one leg? I do.
yingyinNormal.zh: 谁要一条腿的泰迪熊？我要。

yingyinNormal.en: It was sick, malnourished, with a broken leg.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那时候它生着病，营养不良 还断了一条腿。

yingyinNormal.en: They take it off because my leg is better. Is your leg stronger now? It's stronger than it was before. It is a super leg.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我的石膏已经拆掉了，因为我的腿已经康复了。那你的腿现在怎么样了？和以前相比我的腿更结实了，这是条超级结实的腿。

yingyinNormal.en: That dude, there. I need his prosthetic leg. His leg? Yeah.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那边那家伙，我要他的义肢。他的腿？对。

yingyinNormal.en: I've got a bit of an itch. Even if your leg is itching, we can't take the cast off until your leg is better.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我就是感觉有点痒。就算你的腿非常的痒，我们也不能在你的腿康复之前把你的石膏取下来啊。

yingyinNormal.en: By the way, my leg is killing me. Thanks for asking.
yingyinNormal.zh: 顺便说一句，我的腿疼死了，谢谢关心。

yingyinNormal.en: Okay, that is enough, little girl. Let go of my leg. Come on.
yingyinNormal.zh: 好啦，差不多行了，小丫头，放开我的腿，快。

yingyinNormal.en: I broke my leg and they put it in this plaster cast. The plaster cast helps Pedro's leg get better.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我的腿骨折了，然后医生就帮我打了个石膏。石膏能帮助佩德罗的腿恢复得更快。

yingyinNormal.en: Aerodynamics are all off. It's hitting my leg. It's, like, bulky.
yingyinNormal.zh: 完全不符合空气动力学，一直蹭我的腿，还笨重。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh my God. Joey, what did you do after you threw her leg on the fire? I ran.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我的天。你把她的腿丢进火里之后怎么做的？我逃跑了。

yingyinNormal.en: Wait. If she only has one leg, shouldn't she be on can't-kick-starter?
yingyinNormal.zh: 慢着，如果她只有一条腿，她应该去"踢不了人"那种网站才对吧。

yingyinNormal.en: I know a better way to cure hiccups. First, jump up and down three times on one leg.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我知道另一个办法能够治好打嗝，首先你要上上下下跳三次，要单腿。

yingyinNormal.en: I'm going to sit here, so you move the leg. You got a passport? No. I don't even have a driving license.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我要坐这儿，腿移开。有护照吗？没有，我连驾照都没有。

yingyinNormal.en: And then we were fooling around and he started to put his hand up my leg and I kept slapping it away.
yingyinNormal.zh: 后来我们在亲热，他把手放在我的腿上，可我却不停的打开它！

yingyinNormal.en: I mean I like her, I don't want to stop seeing her, but every so often it's like: Hey, you know what, where's your leg?
yingyinNormal.zh: 我喜欢她，想跟她交往下去，不过我忍不住“嘿，说真的，你的腿呢？”

yingyinNormal.en: It is not my leg that is itching. It is my ear. Is it better? Yes, thank you. Lunch time.
yingyinNormal.zh: 其实不是我的腿感觉有点痒，而是我的耳朵感觉有点痒。这样好些了吗？是的，谢谢你。午餐时间到！

yingyinNormal.en: Are you sure? I mean, the nose doesn't light up, but if the corpse is fresh enough, sometimes you can get the leg to jerk.
yingyinNormal.zh: 确定吗？虽然鼻子不会发亮，但如果尸体足够新鲜，偶尔还是能让他腿抽抽呢。

examination_example.sentence: This manual fixation—an indirect by-product of walking upright on two <highlight>legs</highlight>—has helped yield numbers in most cultures, but not all.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 对人工操作的痴迷——人所产生的间接副产品——在大多数文化中帮助产生了数字，但不是全部文化。

examination_example.sentence: Get outside, stretch your <highlight>legs</highlight>, do something cultural, buy yourself something tasty to eat or something pretty to wear.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 出去走走，伸伸腿，做些有文化的事情，给自己买些好吃的或者好看的衣服。

examination_example.sentence: Parents are anxious for advice on how to give their kids a <highlight>leg</highlight> up in the world.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 父母渴望得到如何在世界上帮助孩子的建议。
